ter branches or worktree state changed\n- makes handoff and review timelines cheaper to query\n\nReasons to recompute some association:\n\n- avoids prematurely committing to a wrong relationship\n- keeps durable metadata smaller\n- allows better algorithms later without rewriting old data\n\nMy current take: persist the observation, not the conclusion. Store turn objects\nand environment snapshots. Us\n[TRUNCATED]\nould write enough derived lookup\nentries to make branch/PR review lookup cheap.\n\nA useful split:\n\n- **observations:** persisted source of truth, including transcript records,\n  capture turns, and environment snapshots\n- **derived lookup indexes:** persisted materialized views for fast candidate\n  discovery, safe to rebuild when heuristics change\n- **association result:** computed on read from candidates plus observations,\n  with reasons and heuristic/schema version\n\nThis means association work is split across write and read time:\n\n- **Capture time:** write observations and deterministic index memberships from\n  the current turn snapshot, such as observed branch names, review ids, and\n  change ids.\n- **Read time:** answer association questions by looking up candidate turns from\n  indexes, reading their observations, and scoring/explaining likely related\n  sessions with the current heuristic version.\n\nCapture should not write final inferred relationships such as \"this PR is\nassociated with this session\" or \"this branch was produced by this session.\"\nIt only writes the facts and lookup entries needed to answer those questions\nefficiently later.\n\nThe index is not the association. It is a disposable acceleration structure.\n- depend on `but-ctx` so capture can build the same repository/workspace context\n  as the rest of GitButler\n- prefer reusable `but-api` entry points when they already provide the product\n  shape we need\n- use `but_api::diff::changes_in_worktree` or\n  `but_api::diff::changes_in_worktree_with_perm` for uncommitted worktree files\n- use the same underlying workspace model as `but_api::legacy::workspace::head_info`\n  for stack/branch snapshots, but do not use an API shape that prunes the view\n  to the graph entrypoint; if needed, add an unpruned `but-api` entry point or\n  call `but_workspace::head_info` from an agentlog-local snapshot adapter\n\nThis means the first implementation can capture environment snapshots from the\nsame workspace and diff APIs the app already trusts. If this dependency shape\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T01:52:21.287Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}